05/12/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu announced on Thursday (December 4th) he invited all political parties to negotiate the formation of a new government. 
In his first public statement since Sunday's general elections, he said he hopes politicians will designate a prime minister before December 15th.
Also Thursday, the Central Electoral Bureau announced the final election results. 
In the parliament's lower house, the Basescu-linked Liberal Democratic Party (PDL) won 115 seats, the coalition between the Social Democratic Party (PSD) and the Conservative Party (PC) got 114, the previously ruling National Liberal Party (PNL) took 65 and the Democratic Union of Hungarians in Romania (UDMR) received 22. 
In the Senate, the PDL won 51 seats, the PSD-PC coalition got 49, the PNL 28 and the UDMR 9. 
(Realitatea TV, Ziare, Mediafax, Agerpres, Hotnews, Reuters - 04/12/08)
